  <div class="container-fluid col-md-8 text-start mt-3">
    <p>
      This page contains suggestions for writers and works to read in Chinese
      languages - mostly Mandarin, but there may be exceptions.
    </p>
    <p>
      The writers introduced below include novelists across a range of genres,
      essayists, sociologists, historians, journalists, and others whose works I
      have encountered.
    </p>
    <p class="fst-italic" id="text-box">
      Click <a href="#pagelinks">here</a> to skip to the writers.
    </p>
    <p>
      Since first beginning to learn Chinese, I've sought out reading
      recommendations from friends and native speakers.
    </p>
    <p>
      Over time I've developed my own sense of how and where to seek out what
      I'm interested in - something I tend to take for granted in my native
      language.
    </p>
    <p>
      Tastes differ and there are of course many other writers worth spending
      time with; these are shared here to point towards those I've got something
      out of, and in some cases to promote lesser-known writers or books
      deserving of a broader audience.
    </p>
    <p class="fst-italic" id="text-box">
      For details on where to get hold of Chinese-language books, see
      <a href="/sources">SOURCES</a>
    </p>
