    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="container-fluid col-md-8 text-start mt-3">
    <p>
      Xue Yiwei 薛憶溈 (1964 - ) is an author, academic, and doctor of
      linguistics.
    </p>
    <p>
      His first novel, Desertion 《遺棄》, uses a first-person narrative to
      explore the protagonist's philosophical reflections, as he struggles
      against bureaucratic opposition to quit his vacuous government job.
    </p>
    <p>
      With Shenzheners 《深圳人》, Xue took inspiration from James Joyce's
      Dubliners to produce these short stories on fictional residents of the
      Chinese city.
    </p>
    <!-- Dividing line -->
    <hr class="hr my-4" />
  </div>
