<!-- Yu Hua -->
<div class="container" id="Yu Hua">
  <div class="container-fluid col-md-8 text-center">
    <div>
      <h3>Yu Hua&nbsp;<span class="chinese-heading">余華</span></h3>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="container-fluid col-md-8 text-start mt-3">
    <p>
      Yu Hua 余華 (1960 - ) is an author, and committee member of the Chinese
      Writers Association.
    </p>
    <p>
      To Live 《活著》 follows the hubristic descent into poverty of the
      arrogant son of a land-owning family. As the events of civil war, famine,
      and the Cultural Revolution unfold, the protagonist emerges with a kinder
      outlook even under increasing isolation.
    </p>
    <p>
      As a study of an individual, To Live makes a good compliment to Chen
      Zhongshi's 陳忠實 broader take on similar themes from that era in White
      Deer Plain 《白鹿原》.
    </p>
